snippet.textDisplay:
Please for your own safety consult with a professional HE Mechanic!!!

Heavy equipment is very different from regular passenger vehicles. They're considerably more dangerous, especially if you don't know what you're doing.

NEVER stand under suspended hydraulics that aren't mechanically blocked!

Understand that not all hydraulic fluid is the same, some fluids can be highly toxic and carcinogenic.

Be aware of the dangers involved in driving a rear wheel steering machine.

NEVER loosen any hydraulic lines unless you're 100% sure there is no pressure in them, Google hydraulic injection injury (NSFW).

Fully understand what you are working on, these machines can and will kill/mame you!!

I am new to this channel, I'm not sure what your knowledge level is and I don't mean to offend. You seem like nice guys, and I would hate to hear that one of you got seriously hurt by this machine.
